EventListenr.name: EventListenr
EventListenr.description: EventListenr is a single page web application inspired by Eventbrite, built using Ruby on Rails, React and Redux, and PostgreSQL. Within a rapid development timeline, I implemented features to ensure secure, frontend and backend user authentication, provide users with the ability to create and host events, bookmark events, and purchase tickets to events.

RSpec-Practice.name: RSpec-Practice
RSpec-Practice.description: RSpec is a domain-specific language that is used to test Ruby code. You can write regular Ruby into RSpec files, but you can also use RSpec-specific code. RSpec is used to help make sure that our code does what we want it to. RSpec is made up of statements describing the expected functionality of a piece of code.
